2. The Ratio have been computed as below:

Earnings per Share (Rs.) = $\frac{\text{Restated Profit after tax attributable to equity shareholders for the year}}{\text{Weighted Average Number of equity shares}}$

Diluted Earnings per Share (Rs.) = $\frac{\text{Restated Profit after tax attributable to equity shareholders for the year}}{\text{Weighted Average dilutive Number of equity shares}}$

Return on Net Worth (%) = $\frac{\text{Restated Profit after tax attributable to equity shareholders for the year}}{\text{Net Worth at the end of the year}}$

Net Assets Value per Share (Rs.) = $\frac{\text{Net Worth at the end of the year}}{\text{Total number of equity shares outstanding at the end of the year}}$

3. Net worth for ratios mentioned represents sum of share capital and reserves and surplus (securities premium, debenture redemption reserve, general reserve and surplus in the statement of profit and loss).

4. For computation of Diluted Earnings per Share, effect of dilutive CCDs has been given for all the years presented based on the current estimates of conversion in those respective years.

